16 acres is a 2012 documentary film directed by richard hankin which provides an account of the recovery effort following the september 11 attack , specifically the reconstruction process of the world trade center site .   the name of the documentary refers to the 16 acres of land that the aforementioned site is situated on .   it features interviews with michael bloomberg , george pataki , chris ward , larry silverstein , daniel libeskind , david childs , michael arad , janno lieber , roland betts , rosaleen tallon , and scott raab .